- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper discusses the implementation of AdaptivFloat in a hardware accelerator. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the accuracy of machine learning models through a new data type. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper mentions using AdaptivFloat with state-of-the-art neural network topologies, which could include computer vision models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of deep learning models, which fall under the umbrella of artificial intelligence.
